cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.SI

This paper deals with the security and privacy aspects of string obfuscation in Android applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the development of an open-source tool, which involves software engineering aspects, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) another likely category. The paper also involves program analysis and manipulation techniques, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to identify obfuscated strings, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of a large dataset of Android apps, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
